results.  It's that bad.<br>
<br>
If any of the devs want to look at the parse I'd be happy to email it to them.  If they want to verify the gear I was using as well as the other members in my group(I know they have the means to do this) I again would no problem with that.  If they want a repeat demonstration I'd do it again.<br>
<br>
All I really want is a straight answer.  Is this class intended only for uberguild powergamers at the highest levels or is it supposed to be in good standing throughout the game and for somewhat normal players?  Are they serious about balancing the game properly or is that part of it on the backburner? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zarbonius>Zarbonius</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 269<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/25/03 4:13 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Forget pre-50 balance</span><hr size=1> Ah, post the parse - I haven't had a good solid laugh yet today, and I've gotta meet my daily quota by midnight. <br>
<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=veladorn>Veladorn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist<br>I have needs too!</span><br>  Posts: 1349<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/25/03 5:53 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Forget pre-50 balance</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>All I really want is a straight answer. Is this class intended only for uberguild powergamers at the highest levels or is it supposed to be in good standing throughout the game and for somewhat normal players?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I've always been of the opinion that wizards were amoung the weakest classes in the begining and one of the strongest post 50.  <p><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:blue;font-size:medium;"><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center">Valas Defai</div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.insidiousblood.net/"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;font-size:x-small;">A member of Insidious Blood</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=211027&amp;resize=true" target="top"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:blue;font-size:xx-small;">My Magelo</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jadrax>Jadrax</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 1465<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/25/03 6:07 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Forget pre-50 balance</span><hr size=1> They have already said that all classes should end up even at the end. therefore we really should have some mesure of balance at all levels. Going thruogh phases of being really sucky is not fun. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=95533"><b>Jadrax Darkfire</b></a><br> 
