</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=istari@graffeswizardcompilation>Istari</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 426<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/25/03 6:10 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Forget pre-50 balance</span><hr size=1> you can quad pre-50 but it slows a lot at 45-50... then pillar makes it fast, and at level 65 again am using pillars that do 2% of a mob's life... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zurrenal>Zurren AL</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 641<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/25/03 6:55 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ...</span><hr size=1> The quality of gear pre-50 has increased for melee players over time, while the quality of spells has not scaled up accordingly so.<br>
<br>
Sure, at pre-50 pre-RoK, uber gear was considreed a FBSS, rubicite armour and duel yaks.<br>
<br>
Nowadays, I'm sure a lvl 50 in 'avg' gear is way better then the 'uber' geared up tanks of 99.<br>
<br>
Maybe its time for VI to do some pre-50 magic-class tweaks. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=claudshadowflare>ClaudShadowflare</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist<BR>Has Eddie Murphy's<BR>taste in women</span><br>  Posts: 3815<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/25/03 7:11 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ...</span><hr size=1> I'd like to see the parses- <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>and</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> what focus items / gear the melees vs. the casters in the group had.  I've seen <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>way</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> too many people say &quot;my 41 no-twink wizard couldn't keep up with this 44 monk dual wielding SoD's, wizards are CLEARLY imbalanced!&quot;<br>
<br>
For what it's worth, I think that focus items given to the sub-50 crowd didn't do enough to make up the vast twinkability of a melee class, but it's always better to have hard facts at hand before you go off half-kilt. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nadiar>Nadiar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist<BR>Mistyr Smartipants</span><br>  Posts: 1393<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/25/03 7:24 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ...</span><hr size=1> Well.  The focus items for sub 50 _do_ work 'okay' if you're not looking at twinks.<br>
<br>
But they do nothing to even out for inflation.<br>
<br>
Which could be done by introducing some spells similar to iceflame, but usable by all caster classes. Then slap it on a quested item that is pretty expensive and difficult.<br>
<br>
Effect for wizards would be something like: +10% damage, -20% mana, 10% haste, single DD's only, max level 39.<br>
<br>
Say, clerics: +20% healing, -10% mana, 10% haste,<br>
<br>
I haven't looked into those numbers heavily though. just showing the idea.<br>
<br>
Oh, and let Flowing Thought work at level 1. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=grimstafftheurgist>Grimstaff Theurgist</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elder Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 8260<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/25/03 8:23 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ...</span><hr size=1> There's been a running joke that Wizards were only put in the game originally so there could be Wizard monsters <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Who knows what they are thinking, KEI fixed a lot of the early problems sort of, but they dumped that.  Look, they are not gonna make anything meaningful happen for low level Wizards unless its directly a playtest for EQ2 so this sort of thing leads us nowhere really. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lunaltoadsnatcher>Lunal Toadsnatcher</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 1577<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/26/03 2:19 am)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ...</span><hr size=1> Personally I think the class has periods of balance and imbalance through the 10-50 range.  When we get our new spells, they generally represent a huge increase in power.  However, they don't scale very well.  So at level 34 our new ice nuke is pretty uber but by level 37 we are feeling the pinch.  Melee classes scale up faster and more evenly than casters. especially wizards.<br>
<br>
I think the wizard class is at its weakest in the high teens/low twenties and during almost the entire fourties.  But I think in the low teens and thirties wizards are fairly powerful and desirable to groups.<br>
<br>
My opinion is that they need to scale the damage spells better.  Not provide some new, rare focus item.  Nowadays, with the PoP quests for foci, no young wizard has a good excuse to be without at least MPII, ERII and SHII.  IDII, though - its almost a fuggedaboutit thang.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jadrax>Jadrax</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 1470<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/26/03 4:14 am)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ...</span><hr size=1> They seem to be working a lot on the low level game these days. personally I think some sony exec started playing and decided to make them deal with ll the bullshit. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nadiar>Nadiar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist<BR>Mistyr Smartipants</span><br>  Posts: 1396<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/26/03 5:01 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ...</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>My opinion is that they need to scale the damage spells better. Not provide some new, rare focus item. Nowadays, with the PoP quests for foci, no young wizard has a good excuse to be without at least MPII, ERII and SHII. IDII, though - its almost a fuggedaboutit thang.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> <br>
<br>
Of course they have no reason to be without them.  The problem is that Sony balanced them for their level.<br>
<br>
There is still a lot of twink gear for melee's, but not nearly as much for casters.<br>
<br>
&quot;But we're talking about mudflation!&quot;<br>
<br>
Exactly, take a Centi Long Sword 14/24.  Thats a pretty powerful weapon for a level 20 warrior to be running around with, and if he has one, he could probably have 2.  I have seen them sell for 150 plat each.  Haste could be found for 1000pp, a full set of bronze-ish armor could be aquired by leveling.<br>
<br>
As a wizard, the best you can get is more mana, and some balanced focus items.<br>
<br>
More mana doesn't help wizards do shit in an xp group.  A Fungi is not 'level balanced' nor are any number of haste items. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=throes>Throes</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Flintnilf the Wise</span><br>  Posts: 343<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/26/03 5:16 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ...</span><hr size=1> the main problem at the low end is mana regen. Crap familiars, low specialisation, no spellcasting mastery, nothing. Wizard is going to get one nuke per fight, then sit. Other group members see this, and it stays with them until the endgame; they look at wizards as pretty worthless, not the killing machines we actually are at 60+.<br>
<br>
you need more ft items pre-50. Maybe some items with ft and int, but no +mana. That will force upgrade options when they get to post 50.  <p>Sage Flintnilf Ironori<br>
Harmonium, Xev<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.harmonium.net/filespace/throes/flint3.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=darkpaktgrimsoul>Darkpakt Grimsoul</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 671<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/26/03 5:45 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ...</span><hr size=1> I'd only show this to a dev because posting it here would just tick too many people off.  Personally I've seen enough.  I have two melee characters that will soon be moving through the 50s and I'm not expecting any better results for wizards.<br>
<br>
When SOE announced caster balancing they said they were going to address the gap in power caused by melee weapons and twinking since Kunark.  They have NOT remotely accomplished this from what I've seen.  If they can refute that I'd like to see them do it.  <br>
<br>
Any arguements about soloability are now moot since the group exp patch.  If they want to go that route I can show them what my naked enchanter is capable of with just a stack of SOW potions.  Nevermind that most decently equipped melees can solo up to and beyond the KEI level cap, they would rather get in a group for faster exp as the patch intended. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=eliezeroferudin>Eliezer of Erudin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br>  Posts: 208<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/26/03 7:48 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ...</span><hr size=1> I think one way to add really good items for low level casters without having them unbalance the high end game (by letting Casters get all these 'easy' items at low levels that they keep forever) is to simply let 'Recommended Level' cut BOTH ways.<br>
<br>
So yeah, a Level 10 Caster with an Earring of the Solstice gets crap (I think all the stats are set to 1 or 2 at that level), which supposedly 'balances' twinking.<br>
<br>
So why not create an Item that gives HP, Mana, FT, Focus Effects, etc. with say a Recommended Level of 30.  BUT the HIGHER you get from 30 also DECREASES the stats, the same as it does for people under 30.<br>
<br>
So you'd have a decent item at 25, peaks at 30, is good to say 35, starts to decline towards 40, and after 40 the stats totally blow.<br>
<br>
